choices.text: to be define as colonized, as even recently I can still felt a little bit of shame when someone would mention the fact I am black. People don't know how to react here, wondering how does my family have household name as Fillis here when I can't speak dutch, being "some kind of mixed/bi-racial". being defined by institutions as belonging to africa even though I live in westeuropa ( beiing defined as belongig to germany or french is bad enough, but here it is feeling of being an alien) i can brag about real thing like my accommodation even though i live in a appartment craved in a 1970s concrete rebel with gardens lying around the lobby,  still feeling thankful towards all french and african effort to keep my community and culture alive and not lost into one of many dutch non-indentity people, but realstics talking about my SES is the extreme hard part( SES stands for social economic position for all the typical statisticians) . I can attach myself to my mother's family because i don't know who my father is and my real family is gone and lost and clueless towards where am I. I would love to have some of the capability guys my age could brag about: going to parties, spending hours on a night talking about feelings, having to worry about feeling not fit for certain métier because i was overwhelmed by so few attention received towards my education et passions although I excelled more than expected for me
